100. solstitia. solstitium is, strictly, the time when the sun (sol) appears to stand (stare) still; namely, either in Cancer or Capricorn. It is, however, very generally restricted to “ the summe1·-solstice,” and is so opposed to ὀνῆιηα (= brerima = brevissima), which is the common term for “the winter-solstice.'’ By the figure called synecdoche—the putting of a prominent part, merely, for the whole-solsticium is sometimes put for oestas ‚· just like carina for navis, tectam for domus. It may be so taken here.
